docs.abstract: An acquittal in the second prosecution for a new crime involving “trick orders” raises questions about how the government will pursue future cases.
docs.snippet: An acquittal in the second prosecution for a new crime involving “trick orders” raises questions about how the government will pursue future cases.
docs.lead_paragraph: Federal prosecutors sometimes lose trials, and it is usually not considered too much of a setback. But when the loss involves only the second prosecution for a new crime called “spoofing,” it raises questions about how the government will pursue future cases.

keywords.value: Dodd-Frank Wall Street Reform and Consumer Protection Act (2010)

docs.abstract: Marketers have long had a symbiotic relationship with the social network. But user concerns about data has companies taking a harder look at how they work with Facebook.
docs.snippet: Marketers have long had a symbiotic relationship with the social network. But user concerns about data has companies taking a harder look at how they work with Facebook.
docs.lead_paragraph: Advertisers are the lifeblood of Facebook, and the vast, personal reach of the social network has been a marketer’s dream. But now, some companies are taking a harder look at how they work with it and hunting for skeletons in their own data closets.

headline.main: Facebook’s Current Status With Advertisers? It’s Complicated
headline.print_headline: Data Fallout At Facebook Puts Brands On Full Alert

docs.abstract: As the two companies seek scale to compete in the age of streaming content, they have formed a committee to explore the possibility of a deal.

docs.lead_paragraph: A new chapter opened Thursday in the drama over the future of the $37 billion Redstone media empire, with CBS Corporation and Viacom announcing plans to explore a reunion, reigniting a plan that fizzled a little more than a year ago.

headline.main: Reunited? CBS and Viacom Are Talking About It
headline.print_headline: CBS in Talks With Viacom To Explore A Reunion

docs.abstract: The action, affecting 154,000 vehicles from the 2017 model year, was announced after owners filed safety complaints or shared concerns through social media.

docs.abstract: The brower’s latest update filters out pop-up ads and other annoyances. It also strengthens Google’s grip on the web.
docs.snippet: The brower’s latest update filters out pop-up ads and other annoyances. It also strengthens Google’s grip on the web.
docs.lead_paragraph: As advertising has become more intrusive in recent years, hundreds of millions of web users have installed ad-blocking software to ward off full-page pop-ups, blaring video pitches that start automatically and large ads with unstoppable countdown clocks that obscure the content you actually want to see.

headline.main: Google Chrome Now Blocks Irksome Ads. That’s a Good Thing, Right?
